          en: "CO₂ laser (10,600 nm) is an ablative laser: it literally vaporises skin tissue in the treated zones. It's the most effective technology for:\n— resurfacing deep wrinkles;\n— scar removal (atrophic, post-acne);\n— correcting uneven texture;\n— treating keratosis, nevi, photoageing.\n\nFractional mode (AcuPulse Fractional CO₂):\nTraditional 'fully ablative' CO₂ laser is extremely effective but requires weeks of recovery. Fractional technology (FX) solved this: the laser treats thousands of micro-columns rather than the entire surface, leaving intact 'islands' of skin between them. These islands drive rapid regeneration — recovery is dramatically shorter than with full ablation.\n\nAcuPulse by Lumenis — why specifically:\n— Lumenis invented the original medical CO₂ laser (1990s patent). AcuPulse is that lineage's descendant with updated optics;\n— SmartPulse Technology — controls each micro-pulse duration for precise ablation depth without excess thermal damage;\n— Two modes: AcuPulse Fractional (FX, less downtime) and AcuPulse Total (full ablation, greater effect, greater downtime);\n— FDA-confirmed efficacy for wrinkles, scars and acne scars.\n\nAcuPulse is the most demanding laser procedure in our arsenal. We choose it when the depth of the problem genuinely calls for it — and when the client is prepared for recovery.",
